Welder

Key Responsibilities

Operates equipment safety and use safe work habits;
Maintains a safe and clean working environment by complying with procedures, rules and regulations;
Lays out, positions, aligns and secures parts and assemblies prior to assembly/tacking and or welding using prescribed fixtures and proper work procedures; 
Operates manual or semi-automatic welding equipment to fuse metal segments, using processes such as, gas metal arc, flux-cored arc, shielded metal arc, and submerged arc welding, within the parameters outlined in work procedures;
Recognizes, sets up, operates hand and power tools common to the welding trade;
Examines work pieces for defects and measure work pieces with straightedges or templates to ensure conformance with specifications;
Monitors welding processes to avoid overheating of parts or warping, shrinking, distortion, or expansion of material; 
Determines required welding methods via established work procedures and apply proper welding techniques;
Performs other duties when needed;
Minimum Requirements

High school or equivalent is required;
2 year technical degree or related work experience is preferred;
Must have basic welding aptitude with 2 to 4 years of welding experience;
Must have basic knowledge of bending and forming of metal;
Must be capable of making adjustments to the welding machine for different materials and thickness;
Must be able to operate a cutting torch and a grinder;
Ability to read work orders and bills of material is preferred;
Strong interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills;
Must be attentive to details; neatness and accuracy is important;
Must be able to work with minimum supervision on a flexible schedule;
Must be an enthusiastic self-starter and detailed oriented;
In addition to a great compensation plan, we offer a wide range of benefits, including: medical & dental insurance; vision plan; 401(k) Plan; paid holidays; paid vacation; paid sick time; employee purchase program; and many other perks.

To learn more about us, visit: http://www.procompusa.com/
